    • initializeComponents

      protected abstract void initializeComponents​(Controller controller)
      An abstract initializer that takes in only one controller, this is created for derived classes to inherit from. In particular, within the body, the other initializer with many more arguments can be called. This offers the advantage that wherever this version of initializeComponents is called, only 1 argument is needed, where the logic for initializing all other components (by calling the other version of initializeComponents) can be contained within the derived class.
      Parameters:
      controller -

  • getTableData

    protected abstract java.util.List<java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Object>> getTableData()
